The paper discusses data integration, which is a topic that falls under the database (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The use of quality measures to identify significant data sources and ranking algorithms to return top-k query answers aligns with the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed framework can be applied in software engineering (cs.SE) to improve the quality of query answers in software systems.
